'''Alan Rosenberg''' (born [[October 4]], [[1950s#1950|1950]]) is an American actor who supplied the voice for [[Boba Fett/Legends|Boba Fett]] on the [[National Public Radio|NPR]] adaptation of [[The Empire Strikes Back (radio)|''The Empire Strikes Back'']]. He has played numerous other roles, most notably Eli Levinson in both ''Civil Wars'' and ''L.A. Law''. He was the president of the Screen Actors Guild from 2005 to 2009.

